name: Air-Fried Olives
author: Soup Loving Nicole
summary: These fried olives are salty, spicy, crunchy, and very addictive. Serve with ranch or blue cheese dressing for dipping if desired.
ingredients: 1 (6 ounce) jar jalapeno-stuffed green olives, drained
directions: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Place beaten egg in a separate bowl
Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese in a third bowl
Coat olives first in flour, then in egg, and finally in the bread crumb mixture
Place 1/2 of the olives in the basket of the air fryer
Spray the tops with cooking spray
Cook for 12 minutes, shaking halfway through cook time
Repeat with remaining half of olives
